b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":38,"category_name":"Updates","pr_category_id":"2","title_name":"Update Notification [Addendum]","message":"<div>Update 1.0.6 is now available to download. You may install it right now, otherwise it will be automatically installed at approximately <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1539745200\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Version 1.0.6 brings additional features focused on the new event, as well as various improvements and fixes.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>To celebrate the new event, we will be sending everyone a tenfold summon voucher. This announcement will be modified after these vouchers have been distributed.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Here are some more details about this update:<\/div><div>\\u25a0Event<\/div><div>\\u30fbPreparations for the start of the &ldquo;Trick or Treasure!&rdquo; event<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Additional Features and Improvements:<\/div><div>\\u30fbPlayers can now set Quick-Turn options to on or off in the Game tab of the Options menu.<\/div><div>\\u30fbIn the Upgrade menus, characters, weapons, dragons, and wyrmprints which have been upgraded to their maximum level will be indicated by a mask covering their icons.<\/div><div>\\u30fbAfter a co-op game, the timer to choose whether to battle again with the same players or not has been shortened to 40 seconds.<\/div><div>\\u30fbA camera button has been added to the Continue screen of co-op games, which allows you to spectate the battle.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe movement arrow displayed when sliding your finger along the screen during quests has been shortened.<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe summon appearance rate screen&rsquo;s layout has been adjusted.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Fixes<\/div><div>The following issues have been fixed:<\/div><div>\\u30fbPlayers being unable to progress during the tutorial in Ch. 2\/2-1 &ldquo;The Sylvan Archer&rdquo;<\/div><div>\\u30fbPlayers being unable to progress after creating a room in the co-op tutorial<\/div><div>\\u30fbA co-op game host&rsquo;s co-ability not taking effect when a guest has the strongest version of the same co-ability<\/div><div>\\u30fbQuests not completing when a boss is defeated while asleep or stunned\\u3000<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe display for the stamina recovery times may be reset within a day despite being the same date<\/div><div>\\u30fbGetting stuck when clearing an event quest after the event period has expired<\/div><div>\\u30fbAn error message being displayed when attempting to purchase diamantium to continue a quest<\/div><div>\\u30fbCertain actions during the wyrmprint unbinding animation causing the header and\/or footer to disappear<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Unbind button in the wyrmprint details screen getting unlocked before wyrmprint upgrading becomes available, leading to other possible errors<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Jumpstart Endeavors&rsquo; icon and remaining days disappearing when purchasing the Welcome Pack<\/div><div>\\u30fbHigh Midgardsormr&rsquo;s Trial&rsquo;s tutorial sometimes activating after giving up during Midgardsormr&rsquo;s Trial: Master<\/div><div>\\u30fbHigh Midgardsormr&rsquo;s Trial&rsquo;s treasure trade sometimes getting unlocked even though High Mirdgardsormr&rsquo;s Trial is still locked<\/div><div>\\u30fbCharacters continuing to move on their own when switching from auto-play to manual play while in mid-dash<\/div><div>\\u30fbWith Mikoto as a support character, Flare Stance and Ruin Stance not being displayed when Ravenous Fire (Ruin) hits<\/div><div>\\u30fbBeing unable to move until being struck after canceling a certain attack during Mikoto&rsquo;s Flare Stance<\/div><div>\\u30fbMikoto&rsquo;s stance persisting indefinitely after missing an enemy with Ravenous Fire (Ruin) while either Flare Stance or Ruin Stance is active<\/div><div>\\u30fbRawn&rsquo;s level 2 and 3 Fiend Crush skill not correctly reducing enemy strength<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe following axes&rsquo; level 2 skills not activating their second hit:<\/div><ul><li>Crimsonclaw<\/li><li>Traitor&rsquo;s Despair<\/li><li>The Tyrant<\/li><\/ul><div>\\u30fbThe following types of skills not being used by AI characters:<\/div><ul><li>Buffing skills<\/li><li>Certain recovery skills (recovery skills with additional effects other than regeneration)<\/li><\/ul><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Notes<\/div><div>It may take some time for the update information to be reflected in the store.<\/div><div>You may not be able to perform the update if your device&#39;s data cache is full.<\/div><div>If you are unable to perform the update, please restart your device, wait a few minutes, and try to download it from the store once more.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>To be added <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1539747000\\"><\/span><br><br>The following will be sent to players who started the game by <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1539745200\\"><\/span><br><br>\\u30fbTenfold Summon Voucher x1<br><br>This will be sent to your goodies box when you log in, and you can claim it until <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1540349940\\"><\/span>. This is seven days after it&#39;s sent to your goodie box.<\/div>","start_time":1539676800,"prev_article_id":null,"next_article_id":"58","image_path":"","update_time":1540888544}}}'